He is sensitive and has a foul disposition.

275
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:44,660
Oh.

276
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:47,840
Does he also have a name?

277
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,360
She's totally going to touch your horse when you leave.

278
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:52,560
Tresraxus.

279
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:54,560
Tresraxus.

280
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,600
It's real mouthful.

281
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,279
That is a strong name.

282
00:14:57,279 --> 00:14:58,320
I call him Rax.

283
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:01,840
He dislikes this.

284
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:09,279
Sounds like you two have a strong bond.

285
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,519
Search the castle.

286
00:15:11,519 --> 00:15:12,480
It's complicated.

287
00:15:14,159 --> 00:15:18,560
We'll take care of Rax from a distance.

288
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:23,279
From around a corner, you guys hear Donnie, but you see a red pseudo dragon

289
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:28,399
zip out from around a corner carrying as many dry crackers that he could find.

290
00:15:28,399 --> 00:15:33,120
I found enough food to last at least me for like 20 minutes, so that should be-

291
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:33,620
Oh!

292
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,679
We have friends?

293
00:15:35,679 --> 00:15:38,559
I think sort of instinctually she goes for a weapon and then-

294
00:15:40,959 --> 00:15:41,919
It's all right.

295
00:15:41,919 --> 00:15:42,879
He's with us.

296
00:15:42,879 --> 00:15:44,959
Donnie, get in here and I open up my pouch.

297
00:15:44,959 --> 00:15:46,159
Okay, yeah, yeah.

298
00:15:46,159 --> 00:15:47,600
Just gonna pile the crackers in here.

299
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,720
We got a new friend?

300
00:15:49,759 --> 00:15:50,259
Yes.

301
00:15:50,959 --> 00:15:51,919
Okay, cool.

302
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,640
Horse has a real good vibe about it.

303
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:57,840
I'm gonna hide in here.

304
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:01,600
You would like to go off and search the building?

305
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:07,120
Yeah, I'm just gonna do a quick scan for anything.

306
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:13,120
I think the idea of fighting so hard to get here and then having it be empty is

307
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:17,440
just a little hard to swallow, so she just needs to see it for herself.

308
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,520
You want to make it past the foyer.

309
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:20,640
I get it.

310
00:16:21,279 --> 00:16:30,799
Are there any, aside from people, is there any thing in particular that you might be looking for?

311
00:16:32,159 --> 00:16:39,439
Any sort of writing, any sort of like maybe, you know, what she would really like to know

312
00:16:39,439 --> 00:16:46,240
is what the F happened to the gods and where are they and why the fuck aren't they here.

313
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:51,759
So anything relating to that.

314
00:16:51,759 --> 00:16:57,919
So writing pictograms, diagrams, stained glass things that might have hints,

315
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:04,000
that kind of thing, or I don't know, magical portal that'll come take her

316
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,200
to punch Orcus right in the teeth maybe, something like that.

317
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:10,880
Okay, you go off.

318
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,279
Do you leave the horse where it is?

319
00:17:13,279 --> 00:17:15,120
There's like an elevator that takes you up.

320
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:17,360
He kind of does what he wants, so.

321
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:18,160
Okay, cool.

322
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:24,960
Horse stays, but your new friend Agath walks off and back down the hall.

323
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,760
I want to try to make friends with the horse.

324
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:32,720
Okay, you're welcome to say what the horse does at this point.

325
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:36,560
I guess roll an animal handling check, maybe that sort of.

326
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,040
It was only a 15.

327
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,840
Okay, not so bad.

328
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:44,240
Well no, but I mean with a plus 10 animal handling,

329
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:49,200
I was expecting something a little more exciting, but I rolled an Amy, so.

330
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:56,640
He is very moody and part demon, so he stomps and sort of shakes his head

331
00:17:56,640 --> 00:18:03,279
and huffs and doesn't quite attack, but you do notice that as he huffs,

332
00:18:03,279 --> 00:18:10,160
the breath coming out of his nostrils starts to get like this greenish acrid

333
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,560
like look and smell to it.

334
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:16,560
And like you can sort of like feel like as you try and get closer,

335
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:20,400
it kind of like burns the inside of your throat as you're breathing.

336
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:24,960
You kind of like sort of like if somebody is cooking really hot chili peppers

337
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:27,920
and it just like just like.

338
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,120
I've done that to myself.

339
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:31,040
Yeah, it's sort of like suddenly like, okay.

340
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:31,600
Oh, wow.

341
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,160
Oh, it was like a boy.

342
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:37,360
It's going to be a good one to have on our team.

343
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:41,440
Tell gear turns the end ball.

344
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:45,120
He says, did you happen to scope all those weapons?

345
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,040
Yes, this is a very impressive person.

346
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:52,560
I'm very happy to have on our side if she is on our side.

347
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:58,640
So so tall, so strong down, not, you know, not down with orcas.

348
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:00,480
So that's that's right away.

349
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:01,520
That's a plus.

350
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:05,040
It has been so long since we have seen any creature

351
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:07,359
not immediately trying to kill us.

352
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,639
It's refreshing.

353
00:19:08,639 --> 00:19:12,399
It's why I was a little standoffish at first.

354
00:19:12,399 --> 00:19:14,000
You know, we've been burned before.

355
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,440
Yeah, no, I totally get it.

356
00:19:16,879 --> 00:19:21,119
Plus, I mean, just kind of really just manhandled that door with you behind it.

357
00:19:21,119 --> 00:19:23,839
Really just pushed it and you just slid on the floor.

358
00:19:23,839 --> 00:19:26,480
It was real, just real slick.

359
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:30,399
And then Fia starts to like scuff her shoe, like where it was trying to recreate

360
00:19:30,399 --> 00:19:32,240
how slippery it was, even though it wasn't slippery.

361
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,279
It's not slippery at all.

362
00:19:33,279 --> 00:19:37,200
In fact, you can't scuff them at all across that with your own strength.

363
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,519
Dust blew in and it's me, you know.

364
00:19:39,519 --> 00:19:39,759
Yeah.

365
00:19:39,759 --> 00:19:40,160
Oh, yeah.

366
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:41,519
No, happens to the best of us.

367
00:19:41,519 --> 00:19:43,920
It kind of rolls his eyes in the background.

368
00:19:47,039 --> 00:19:49,759
We follow Agatha back down this hallway.

369
00:19:51,119 --> 00:19:55,599
The first hallway that you walk down, it follows the outside of the tower

370
00:19:56,319 --> 00:20:02,799
in almost a circular fashion for quite a ways before coming to a singular open door,

371
00:20:02,799 --> 00:20:07,200
probably because the other three would have been coming and going from it,

372
00:20:07,919 --> 00:20:13,359
which leads into just a small box of a room with a series of lights on the wall.

373
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:16,319
Are they like magical lights?

374
00:20:17,039 --> 00:20:17,440
Yeah.

375
00:20:18,159 --> 00:20:20,319
Yeah, she can tell.

376
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:21,680
She knows magic stuff.

377
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:22,180
Yeah.

378
00:20:23,919 --> 00:20:28,079
Can I roll some kind of like history or a kind of check on what they are?

379
00:20:29,039 --> 00:20:30,720
Would you know how an elevator works?

380
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:34,319
No, I don't think those are very common where she's from.

381
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,360
They're not.

382
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,319
She's going to spend a lot of time.

383
00:20:39,519 --> 00:20:42,079
I didn't prepare to detect magic, but...

384
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:47,039
You can definitely roll an arcana or even like a history,

385
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:50,400
because you would have gained some knowledge of the tower itself.

386
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,960
A little bit better at history, but that ain't good.

387
00:20:53,759 --> 00:20:54,960
That's a 10.

388
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:57,440
You stare in this room for quite a while.

389
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:58,000
Yeah.

390
00:20:58,079 --> 00:21:04,240
What would Agoth do, not knowing exactly what to do, in order to get movement?

391
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:11,920
Shield up, slowly approaching very cautiously, stepping back a bit,

392
00:21:13,839 --> 00:21:21,200
itching forward again, considering casting a spell, but deciding against it,

393
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:26,079
going to take out maybe like a lance.

394
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:32,559
Just make it really awkward and like, start poking things with the lance.

395
00:21:33,119 --> 00:21:38,079
As you poke like one of these lights, it illuminates brighter, and then the door begins to close.

396
00:21:39,759 --> 00:21:42,799
That is very nerve-wracking, small spaces, not great, but...

397
00:21:43,839 --> 00:21:45,519
Then vertical movement starts.

398
00:21:46,319 --> 00:21:47,519
I think she's very motion sick.

399
00:21:49,519 --> 00:21:51,919
This is all we're doing for the rest of this episode.

400
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:59,279
Agoth is on the elevator, pressed against the wall.

401
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:03,920
Doesn't take very long, and then the movement slows, and then comes to a stop,

402
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:09,200
and you hear a small ding, and then the door slowly slides open, and you're on

403
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,960
there's an entirely different hallway ahead of you.

404
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:21,120
She's going to take full stealth crouch, creeping forward at a low crawl.

405
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:25,279
Out of the doors very quickly, in case they are closing again.

406
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:33,279
Gonna maybe prop them open with something, and then very carefully,

407
00:22:33,279 --> 00:22:37,440
very hunter-in-the-wood style, make her way down this hallway.

408
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:42,960
It's a dimly lit hallway, and there's several doors along the way.

409
00:22:43,759 --> 00:22:48,480
As you look in the first one, it looks like what were at one point living quarters.

410
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:51,839
A lot of the sheets and beds have kind of been tossed.

411
00:22:51,839 --> 00:22:55,599
Personal items seem to have been cleared off of shelves.

412
00:22:55,599 --> 00:23:03,279
There's the occasional non-important book or journal that's been

413
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:07,360
scrawled in a couple pages, but as you kind of flip through some of these,

414
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:15,920
there's no real information regarding the gods, or a portal, or anything.

415
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:22,800
It's all just, it seems like all before information, when people were living happy lives.

416
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:28,720
So does it look like this place has been abandoned for that long then?

417
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,240
Like 10 odd years, or?

418
00:23:31,279 --> 00:23:33,680
Not 10 years, I don't think.

419
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:39,759
It looks like it's been, like dust has started to really pile up on shelves and stuff.

420
00:23:39,759 --> 00:23:42,160
There appears to be fresh footprints,

421
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:48,240
but what you can absolutely deduce is that they match the three that you met downstairs.

422
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:51,200
On this floor specifically, you don't find anything else.

423
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:59,200
So I'd say it's been abandoned for anywhere from between one and three years.

424
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:06,160
Okay. Are there stairs, or is the elevator the only way to traverse?

425
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:12,880
Yeah, as you walk around, the only way you find is this dinging box.

426
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:13,600
It is the way.

427
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:17,519
She'll like scowl at it and kind of grit her teeth and like, you know,

428
00:24:17,519 --> 00:24:21,840
just sort of do a sequential, I think she's figured out that the button,

429
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:25,440
how the buttons work, no longer requires the lance.

430
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:28,560
Still deeply suspicious. Does not like it.

431
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:33,440
Does not like this experience of moving like under something else's volition,

432
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:37,360
but will scope the rest of the tower in the same way.

433
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:44,799
Yeah, you go floor by floor until you reach a floor about midway up this series of lights,

434
00:24:44,799 --> 00:24:49,279
and the doors swing open and you find that there are no footsteps leading out.

435
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:50,480
Okay, more promising.

436
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,480
Which leads you to believe that it was a room,

437
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:55,360
or at least a floor that was missed by the group before you.

438
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:56,400
We are not thorough.

439
00:24:57,279 --> 00:25:02,240
You walk out and into this, what looks more like a large cathedral,

440
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:11,599
and you do see along the walls, which are the swirling beacon up on top,

441
00:25:11,599 --> 00:25:20,799
illuminates these stained glass windows, and in them are just backdrops.

442
00:25:23,039 --> 00:25:26,480
From the looks of the room, and as you kind of go around,

443
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:29,359
you see that there are like placards beneath all of them,

444
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:34,160
and they have the names of, at the very least, the lawful gods.

445
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:38,960
But in those stained glass images, you do not see those gods.

446
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,480
Hmm, interesting.

447
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:53,840
Yeah, I will sort of like do a full circuit of all of the windows and the cathedral space,

448
00:25:53,840 --> 00:26:00,400
and if there is nothing else to find except the god's continued absence,

449
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:03,600
then I will eventually make my way back down.

450
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:14,320
In the meantime, I feel like my lovely horse may have racks like snacks,

451
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:21,200
so he may be trying to muzzle his way into that bag to take some of those crackers

452
00:26:21,759 --> 00:26:23,519
that we're flying past.

453
00:26:23,519 --> 00:26:27,759
Super excited about it, and it's just feeding him all these crackers like,

454
00:26:27,759 --> 00:26:29,840
Hey! Hey, those are my crackers! Hey, no!

455
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:30,319
You'll be fine!

456
00:26:30,319 --> 00:26:31,360
Get it away from the demon beast!

457
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:34,240
I'm making a friend, Donnie, you know how important this is to me!

458
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,920
No! They're my crackers, I found them!

459
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:38,080
You walk around the corner as this is happening.

460
00:26:39,039 --> 00:26:39,840
They're mine!

461
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,279
It's fine, you're making a friend.

462
00:26:41,279 --> 00:26:47,680
Rex is like just sort of like snorting and like bearing his teeth at the pseudo dragon.

463
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:50,799
Ugh! I can snort and bear my teeth too!

464
00:26:50,799 --> 00:26:51,039
Hey!

465
00:26:51,039 --> 00:26:53,120
Oh, you got something there, right?

466
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,000
It's a cracker!

467
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,759
No, it's not.

468
00:26:55,759 --> 00:26:56,160
Okay.

469
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:56,960
Stop snorting.

470
00:26:57,519 --> 00:26:57,600
No!

471
00:26:57,600 --> 00:27:00,080
Get in the bag, Donnie, you're embarrassing yourself.

472
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,360
Your horse is a menace.

473
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:04,880
Yes, that is the point.

474
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:09,920
Did you find anything that you were looking for?

475
00:27:12,480 --> 00:27:16,480
I simply found that here, too, the gods are absent.

476
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:20,080
What gods specifically are you looking for?

477
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:26,560
Well, any of them would be nice, but...

478
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:27,600
Yeah, fair enough.

479
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,720
Eldath and I once had...

480
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:34,640
Well, I was once her cleric.

481
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:41,600
Before, being a cleric was not a thing anymore.

482
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:44,480
Right.

483
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:54,319
Well, let's go kick some orcish ass and find some gods in the Arkane Brotherhood.

484
00:27:54,799 --> 00:27:55,120
Yes.

485
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:58,400
I'm sorry, I'm still feeding crackers.

486
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,440
They're my crackers.

487
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:08,559
We have only arrived here not too long ago in this time and place.

488
00:28:08,559 --> 00:28:15,279
In this time?

489
00:28:17,759 --> 00:28:19,279
Yes, we were...

490
00:28:21,759 --> 00:28:24,159
I guess in the before times?

491
00:28:24,879 --> 00:28:28,879
We're from the past, but isn't technically everybody from the past?

492
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:30,240
No.

493
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,240
What if you think about it, though?

494
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:41,039
Well, turns out these ones were fighting a lich, and then they essentially didn't realize

495
00:28:41,039 --> 00:28:42,559
ten years had passed.

496
00:28:42,559 --> 00:28:47,359
You say that like we lost track of time in a floating pyramid told here.

497
00:28:47,359 --> 00:28:52,240
That's not what I meant, but just from the time they went into the flying pyramid

498
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:56,720
and the time they came out, ten years everywhere else had passed.

499
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,400
Not a lot of time had passed for them.

500
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:02,000
And the ten most terrible years.

501
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:08,000
And in all of this, I had not even thought to consider that the gods had all disappeared.

502
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,160
You are a cleric.

503
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:10,480
I am.

504
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:14,720
For whom?

505
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,920
I follow the path of the light.

506
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:22,880
I have a spirit, a quarry spirit called Ithgara.

507
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:26,720
It is, I think, somewhat different than a cleric.

